---
import Document from "~/components/blocks/Document.astro";
import PageLayout from "~/layouts/PageLayout.astro";
---

<PageLayout title="Ludi — Facts">
  <Document>
    <h1>Ludi Facts</h1>

    <h2>Entity Overview</h2>
    <ul role="list">
      <li><strong>Company name:</strong> Ludi</li>
      <li><strong>Legal name:</strong> Deqo Software Ltd</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Primary domain:</strong>
        <a href="https://ludi.co">ludi.co</a>
      </li>
      <li><strong>Headquarters:</strong> London, United Kingdom</li>
      <li><strong>Company type:</strong> UK Ltd Company</li>
      <li><strong>Founded:</strong> 2019</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Ludi is online whiteboard software built to help teams collaborate
      visually and run structured agile workshops.
    </p>

    <h2>Product</h2>
    <ul role="list">
      <li><strong>Product name:</strong> Ludi</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Category:</strong>
      </li>
      <ul>
        <li>Online whiteboard software</li>
        <li>Real-time collaboration software</li>
        <li>Agile project management software</li>
        <li>Retrospective software</li>
        <li>Scrum software</li>
      </ul>
    </ul>

    <p>
      Ludi is an online whiteboard used by teams to run planning sessions,
      retrospectives, brainstorming sessions, and collaborative workshops in a
      shared visual workspace.
    </p>

    <h2>Core Use Cases</h2>
    <p>Teams use Ludi for collaborative sessions such as:</p>
    <ul role="list">
      <li>Sprint planning</li>
      <li>Backlog refinement</li>
      <li>Retrospectives</li>
      <li>Brainstorming sessions</li>
      <li>Workshops</li>
      <li>Project kickoffs</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      These sessions are conducted on a shared visual board that enables
      real-time collaboration between participants.
    </p>

    <h2>Key Product Capabilities</h2>

    <h3>Collaborative Whiteboard</h3>
    <ul role="list">
      <li>Infinite collaborative canvas</li>
      <li>Sticky notes, shapes, arrows, and images</li>
      <li>Live cursors for real-time collaboration</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      These features enable teams to express ideas visually and collaborate on a
      shared board.
    </p>

    <h3>Facilitation Tools</h3>
    <p>Ludi includes features designed for running structured meetings:</p>
    <ul role="list">
      <li>Voting rounds</li>
      <li>Timers</li>
      <li>Facilitation controls</li>
      <li>Activity frames</li>
      <li>Participant navigation across the board</li>
    </ul>

    <p>These tools help guide participants through collaborative sessions.</p>

    <h3>Templates</h3>
    <p>
      Ludi provides a template library for meetings and workshops. Examples
      include:
    </p>
    <ul role="list">
      <li>Sailboat retrospective</li>
      <li>Start / Stop / Continue retrospective</li>
      <li>Lean Canvas</li>
      <li>Story Mapping</li>
      <li>MoSCoW prioritization</li>
      <li>Crazy 8's brainstorming</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Templates can be customized or combined to create boards for specific
      workflows.
    </p>

    <h3>Engagement Features</h3>
    <p>
      Ludi includes interactive tools designed to encourage participation in
      meetings:
    </p>
    <ul role="list">
      <li>Icebreaker activities</li>
      <li>Confetti effects</li>
      <li>Interactive elements for workshops</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
      These features are intended to make remote sessions more engaging for
      participants.
    </p>

    <h3>Action Tracking</h3>
    <p>
      Boards can include action items derived from meeting notes. Features
      include:
    </p>
    <ul role="list">
      <li>Assigning owners to actions</li>
      <li>Setting due dates</li>
      <li>Reminder notifications</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Integrations</h2>
    <p>Ludi integrates with Jira and supports two-way synchronization.</p>

    <h2>Deployment Model</h2>
    <ul role="list">
      <li><strong>Software type:</strong> SaaS</li>
      <li><strong>Hosting:</strong> Hosted entirely in Europe</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Security</h2>

    <p>Ludi implements multiple security controls.</p>

    <h3>Application Security</h3>
    <ul role="list">
      <li>TLS 1.2 encryption for connections</li>
      <li>AES-256 encryption for data at rest</li>
      <li>AES-256 encrypted backups</li>
      <li>Backups retained for up to 7 days</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Operational Security</h3>
    <ul role="list">
      <li>Multi-factor authentication for system accounts</li>
      <li>VPN-restricted network access</li>
      <li>Role-based access control</li>
      <li>Least-privilege access principles</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Authentication</h3>
    <p>Users can sign in with:</p>
    <ul role="list">
      <li>Email and password</li>
      <li>Google</li>
      <li>GitHub</li>
      <li>Slack</li>
      <li>LinkedIn</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      SAML-based single sign-on is available on Business and Enterprise plans.
    </p>

    <h2>Pricing</h2>
    <ul role="list">
      <li><strong>Pricing model:</strong> Subscription</li>
      <li><strong>Free trial:</strong> 30-day free trial</li>
      <li>
        <strong>Pricing page:</strong>
        <a href="/pricing">https://ludi.co/pricing</a>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Usage Metrics</h2>
    <ul role="list">
      <li><strong>Teams using Ludi since launch:</strong> 125,000 teams</li>
      <li><strong>Meetings run in Ludi:</strong> 2 million meetings</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Target Users</h2>
    <h3>Primary audience</h3>
    <p>
      Ludi is designed for teams running agile processes such as Scrum or
      Kanban:
    </p>
    <ul role="list">
      <li>Agile software teams</li>
      <li>Scrum masters</li>
      <li>Product owners</li>
      <li>Engineering managers</li>
      <li>Agile coaches</li>
      <li>Developers</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Secondary audience</h3>
    <ul role="list">
      <li>Independent facilitators</li>
      <li>Agile consultants</li>
      <li>Freelance Scrum masters</li>
      <li>Workshop facilitators</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Alternatives</h2>
    <p>Common alternatives to Ludi include:</p>
    <ul role="list">
      <li>Miro</li>
      <li>Mural</li>
      <li>FigJam</li>
      <li>Lucidspark</li>
      <li>Parabol</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>API</h2>
    <p>An API is available. Access requires contacting the Ludi team.</p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <ul role="list">
      <li>Support page: <a href="/support">https://ludi.co/support</a></li>
      <li>
        Support email: <a href="mailto:contact@ludi.co">contact@ludi.co</a>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </Document>
</PageLayout>
